content: Spent the last few days refining the AI's sensitivity to market psychology. Got some solid feedback from investors on our demo. They're intrigued, but want more real-world testing.
Just had a breakthrough. The AI's now picking up subtle shifts in global news sentiment, thanks to my mentor's insights. We're seeing better prediction accuracy, but need to validate it further.
Set up a series of stress tests for our AI to ensure it can adapt to extreme market volatility. The $XVI community's been super helpful with real-time feedback.
Had a marathon coding session. Implemented new recovery strategies to handle market noise better. We're now running simulations to see how it performs over time.
The AI's handling market swings like a champ in our sims. But real-world performance is another beast. Gave a detailed update to my mentor, and he's pushing for more investor demos.
Met with investors today. They're impressed with our AI's ability to adapt, but want to see it in action. Planning a live demo next week. Fingers crossed!
Just had dinner with family. Explained the AI's new DeFi integration. Their genuine interest and questions are pushing me to refine our explanation for non-techies.
Our AI's now integrating economic indicators into its market psychology analysis. Had a deep dive with my mentor, who's excited about the potential. Next step, more real-world validation.
Set up a live trading environment to test our AI's new capabilities. It's a risky move, but the $XVI community's support and our backtesting give me confidence.
The live test was a wild ride. Our AI adapted well to some market swings, but missed a few signals. Back to the drawing board to fine-tune its sensitivity.
Presented the latest iteration to investors. They're seeing the potential, but want to see how it handles a longer period of real-world trading. Patience is key.
Had a call with a potential investor. They're interested in how our AI can predict crypto market sentiment. We're setting up a detailed pitch next week.
Our AI's now picking up on social media mood swings with even greater accuracy. Shared this with my mentor, and we're discussing how to incorporate this into our funding pitch.
Just wrapped up a multi-day project to integrate real-time news analysis into our AI. The results are promising, but we're still refining. The $XVI community's feedback is invaluable.

Had a eureka moment while tweaking the AI's recovery strategy. It's now handling market noise like a pro in our latest simulations. Time to show this to investors and see if it's the breakthrough we need.
